ce:section.ce:para:
All the materials were obtained from Aldrich or Merck and used without additional purifications. The reaction process of the products was monitored by TLC using analytical silica gel plates. FT-IR spectra were provided on a Shimadzu FT-IR 8300 spectrophotometer using pressed potassium bromide disks. The 1H nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR; 250 MHz) and 13C NMR (62.9 MHz) spectra were obtained with a Bruker Avance DPX-250 MHz spectrometer in chloroform (CDCl3) or dimethylsulfoxide (DMSO-d

                           6
                        ) as solvent and tetramethylsilane as an internal reference. The XRD patterns were obtained on a Rigaku Smart-Lab X-ray diffractometer. The magnetic properties of NPs were measured using Lake Shore 7407 VSM. FESEM images were achieved by scanning electron microscopyFEI Quanta 200. TEM images were performed on a Philips EM208S transmission electron microscope. EDX spectroscopy was performed using a FESEM, JEOL 7600 F microscope equipped with an EDX spectrometer from Oxford Instruments. All melting points were measured using an electrothermal melting point of 9100 in capillary tubes. Thermogravimetric-differential thermal analysis (TG-DTA) of the sample was performed on a TA Q600 model with a heating rate of 10 ℃/min in the temperature range of 25–1000 ℃ under a nitrogen atmosphere. Inductively coupled plasma (IСР) experiments were conducted with a simultaneous model ICP-OES Vista-PRO CCD from Varian.
